⚡ Control Pilot (CP) Communication in EV Charging

A comprehensive guide to IEC 61851 Control Pilot (CP) communication, PWM signaling, EV state detection, and charger-to-vehicle interaction.

📖 Overview

The Control Pilot (CP) is the primary communication interface between an Electric Vehicle (EV) and an Electric Vehicle Supply Equipment (EVSE) as defined in IEC 61851 and SAE J1772.

Before any power is delivered, the CP line ensures:

Safe vehicle detection
Charging readiness verification
Maximum current advertisement
Cable integrity validation
Fault detection and protection

Without successful CP communication, charging cannot begin.

