State B (Vehicle Connected)

When the connector is inserted, resistor R2 (2.74 kΩ) is connected between CP and PE.

This creates a voltage divider with R1 (1 kΩ) located inside the charger.

Calculation:

Vcp = 12 × (2.74 / (1 + 2.74))

Vcp ≈ 8.8 V

Rounded to:

9 V

The charger interprets this as:

State B = Vehicle Present////
